# Git tracks only Symphony's framework code. Everything below is runtime, private,
# or machine-local data that must NEVER be committed — these rules live in the repo
# itself so the boundary holds for every clone, CI run, and collaborator, not just
# whoever set a machine-global core.excludesFile.

# Dependencies
node_modules/

# Build output & caches
dist/
build/
coverage/
.vite/
*.tsbuildinfo

# Symphony runtime & private data
# The SQLite DB (issues + ask transcripts) and uploaded attachments live under data/
# (DATA_DIR); per-issue worktrees live under workspace_root (a tmpdir). The *.db / *.sqlite
# rules are defense-in-depth in case SYMPHONY_DATA_DIR / SYMPHONY_DB_PATH points inside the repo.
data/
*.db
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3
*.db-wal
*.db-shm

# Secrets & env
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
*.local

# Local agent / editor / OS config (machine-local, not shared project config)
# Only the per-user Claude local settings are ignored — a managed repo may legitimately
# commit .claude/skills/ or a shared .claude/settings.json, so do NOT blanket-ignore .claude/.
# Agent conversation transcripts live in the user's home (~/.claude/projects/...), never in this repo.
.claude/settings.local.json
WORKFLOW.md
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Logs
*.log
logs/
npm-debug.log*
